---
title: Teriyaki Steak with Wasabi Mashed Potatoes & Roasted Broccoli
description: Hankering for a plate of good ol’ steak and potatoes? We’ve got your back. This recipe takes the classics above and beyond with a few flavorful twists. There’s seared steak, creamy wasabi-spiked mashed potatoes, and sesame-sprinkled roasted broccoli. And on top? Sweet teriyaki sauce and fresh ginger create a rich elixir you’ll want to drizzle over everything. And now you can!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/teriyaki-steak-6ce73db1.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/teriyaki-steak-5dfd129d14ead61489462f43-2f18c1b7.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Japanese
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/teriyaki-steak-5dfd129d14ead61489462f43
nutrition:
  calories: 700 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 57 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1390 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces, if necessary. Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender and browned at edges, ~{15-20%minutes}. Meanwhile, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Boil until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While potatoes cook, place @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} in a #large dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring often, until golden brown and toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Once potatoes are tender, reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to #pot{}. Add @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and @wasabi paste{1%teaspoon} to taste. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and pepper. Cover to keep warm.

Pat @steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season generously all over with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in pan used for sesame seeds over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Heat same pan over medium heat. Add @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) and as much ginger as you like. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in any resting juices from steak. Add @teriyaki sauce{8%tablespoon}; bring to a simmer. Turn off heat. Season with salt and pepper. Divide potatoes and broccoli between plates. Slice steak against the grain; arrange over potatoes. Spoon sauce over steak. Top with as many sesame seeds as you like.